    "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nThis happening because the test [here](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/cf97d2485fc3f6d4df1b79a3ea183e24c272215e/lua/lspconfig/ui/lspinfo.lua#L141) is failing.\r\n```lua\r\n      if root_dir == nil or fname:sub(1, root_dir:len()) ~= root_dir then\r\n        matched = false\r\n      end\r\n```\r\n\r\n[fname](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/cf97d2485fc3f6d4df1b79a3ea183e24c272215e/lua/lspconfig/ui/lspinfo.lua#L194) is the always associated with the original buffer so this test is always failing when finding a client that does not have the same root. I'm not sure why we can't rely purely on the root_dir from the client and remove this test ?\r\n",
